<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="324" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,942,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1050,1076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Irfan &amp; Wang &amp; Zhao &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Irfan &amp; Wang &amp; Zhao &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,549,1051,1076]" class="Arachnida" family="Pimoidae" genus="Pimoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yajiangensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[329,549,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">Pimoa yajiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[556,619,1051,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[556,619,1051,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Xu &amp; Li, 2007" authorityName="Xu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2007" box="[746,1062,1051,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Pimoidae" genus="Pimoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reniformis">
<emphasis box="[746,889,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">P. reniformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Xu, X. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[896,1062,1051,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324" pagination="483 - 502" refId="ref5323" refString="Xu, X. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2007) Taxonomic study of the spider family Pimoidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from China. Zoological Studies, 46, 483 - 502." type="journal article" year="2007">Xu &amp; Li, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Xu, X. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[1077,1297,1051,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324" pagination="483 - 502" refId="ref5323" refString="Xu, X. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2007) Taxonomic study of the spider family Pimoidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from China. Zoological Studies, 46, 483 - 502." type="journal article" year="2007">Xu &amp; Li 2007: 493</bibRefCitation>
, figs 42–47) in having similar dorsal and ventral plates, which become narrow posteriorly and having an oval mark on the dorsal plate. However, the new species can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1115,1123,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Pimoidae" genus="Pimoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[951,1024,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">Pimoa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by a heart-shaped epigynal ventral plate and the copulatory ducts with two turns directed dorso-ventrally before entering the spermathecae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,1268,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-379@6.[151,1435,1268,1780]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pimoa yajiangensis n. sp., female holotype. A, Epigynum, ventral view; B, Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars, A, B, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5881226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5881226/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
