<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="325" pageId="6" pageNumber="324" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1929,2028]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="325" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,440,1929,1955]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">Description. Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[457,559,1929,1955]" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[572,662,1929,1955]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,882,906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,858]" captionTargetId="figure-32@9.[151,1435,181,858]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Habitus of Pimoa spp., dorsal view.A, Male holotype of P. pingwuensis n. sp.; B, Female paratype of P. pingwuensis n. sp.; C, Female holotype of P. yajiangensis n. sp.; D, Male holotype of P. zekogensis n. sp. Scale bars, A–D, 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5881234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5881234/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="324">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
): Total length 10.24. Carapace 4.10 long, 3.09 wide. Abdomen 6.84 long, 5.64 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.22, ALE 0.21, PME 0.21, PLE 0.22; AME–AME 0.16, AME– ALE 0.19, PME–PME 0.18, PME–PLE 0.24. Carapace brownish with black lateral margins; thoracic fovea and radial grooves distinct; sternum brownish. Abdomen black with yellowish transverse chevron bands. Legs brownish with black annulations. Leg measurements: I: 21.16 (6.23, 7.08, 5.42, 2.43); II: 19.07 (5.62, 6.33, 4.87, 2.25); III: 14.14 (4.32, 4.44, 3.62, 1.76); IV: 18.56 (5.67, 6.17, 4.73, 1.99).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="325">
Epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[329,448,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[151,1421,1268,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-379@6.[151,1435,1268,1780]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pimoa yajiangensis n. sp., female holotype. A, Epigynum, ventral view; B, Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars, A, B, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5881226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5881226/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="325">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
): heart-shaped; ventral and dorsal plates posteriorly narrow; copulatory openings distinct; Copulatory ducts with two turns and not fused; spermathecae round, touching each other; fertilization ducts oriented laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,429]" box="[199,392,367,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,367,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="325">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
